title: The Dennis Prager Radio Show JULY-10-2013 WED
description:
The Dennis Prager Radio Show JULY-10-2013 WED







Dennis Prager Radio Show

Prager 20130710  3 Not Justified

Prager H3: A disturbing factor in the trial of George Zimmerman is the wide spread belief
 that if he is acquitted, there will be riots.

 The anti-riot campaign administered by local law enforcement should be unnecessary

 some people seem to only want justice when it fits their agenda,

 and not for the sake of justice.


Prager 20130710  2 Male/ Female Hour: What is Femininity?

Prager H2: What traits do women possess that make them feminine?

 Dennis has a couple of ideas and callers weigh in.


Prager 20130710  1 Extreme Candidate Makeovers

Prager H1: Elliot Spitzer, running for NYC Comptroller, and Anthony Weiner, running for NYC Mayor,

 are both front runners.

 Lela Gilbert, freelance journalist, joins the show to discuss her new book: 

   Saturday People, Sunday People: Israel Through the Eyes of a Christian Sojourner.
